RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $1,675 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLING BLING BLING broke a step slow, moved up the fence in hand to take command a hundred yards from the gate, set a well measured pace, opened a clear advantage in upper stretch while still in hand and drew away convincingly. TAPITURE JONES prompted the pace from two wide throughout, failed to gain on his stablemate but kept on willingly to hold the place. GUITAR BOY reserved off the pacesetter in the second flight, rallied three wide in the turn and steadily gained ground on the runner-up in the lane. RED SUMMERBIRD tracked the paced from the fence in striking distance and failed to gain ground down the stretch when called upon. I'M A COWBOY went evenly and never posed a threat. MORO OUTLAW trailed throughout as a non-factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 5F Turf CR: 76. Claiming Purse 18500. (PLUS UP TO $3,700 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to ru n this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAMARADERIE chased the pack from the inside, then bid on the turn, came out five wide and surged down the lane to be up at the wire proving best. FROSTY BREW vied for the lead while four wide, then took command leaving the bend, held the lead gamely in the early stretch then was out finished in the end and was second best. NIGHT ORB vied for the lead while three wide, then settled back along the inside throughout the turn, then rallied in late stretch to close strongly for the show prize. OKIE CODE chased the pace while two wide, was in a steady drive throughout, came put six wide heading into the lane and was closing well in the end. CASHMERE DANCER settled along the inside in back of the pack, then bid on the turn to rally in the late stretch but needed more in the end. PIECE OF ME lead the way early then vied to keep the lead with outer rivals on the turn, was in a strong drive in the early stretch then gave way in the final furlong. BIDOFHONEY vied for the lead while three wide, was in a hard drive throughout the turn and into the stretch then gave way in the end. ATTA MOY GIRL trailed throughout the course and was no factor.

JIM AND JIM unhurried early while caught three wide in the first turn, steadily gained ground down the backside while dropping to the fence, angled out for the drive and closed well to be second best. INFINITE MORO reserved off the pace in mid-pack to the final bend, circled four wide coming home and showed late interest gaining in the stretch to be up for the show. GAMMA RAY raced well off the pace near the rear of the field to upper stretch and made up ground in the stretch. MR OKLAHOMA CITY slow early to be the trailer to the head of the lane and passed tired rivals late. NOOGE sped to the lead, set a contested pace to midway on the turn and faded coming home. PROUD TO SERVE pressed the pace for a half mile and steadily gave way. SCHOENHARDT chased the leaders for a half mile and came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CANDY TAP vied for the lead from the inside into the turn, then drew away in the early stretch to duel grudgingly with an outer rival down the lane and was up at the wire to prove best. GLITZ AND GLAMOUR vied for the lead while three deep into the bend, then inched away to duel with an inner rival in the stretch drive and was out finished in the end. SHINING EXAMPLE broke outwardly at the start and bumped rival, then vied between rivals into the turn then gave way in the early stretch and held onto the show prize. CRANKY SHEILA chased the pace while two wide, made a mild bid on the turn, came out four wide at the top of the lane then flattened out in late stretch. FREE DROP GYPSY was in tight early, steadied then was out run and no menace. RABBIT HOLE was bumped at the start, then trailed behind the field throughout and was no factor.

(PLUS UP TO $6,900 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $30,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; O lder, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since March 15, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since December 15, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000 (Maiden Or Claiming Races Not Considered In Allowances). (If Deemed inadvisabl e by management to run thisrace over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOHAN ZOFFANI (IRE) stalked the leaders from the rail down the backside, waited for racing room through the turn while patiently handled, angled out in upper stretch to the clear and closed rapidly to be up late in the drive in a game effort. ENGLANDER pressed the pace from between horses through the first turn and down the backside dueling on the lead, pulled to the front midway on the far turn, took control in upper stretch but could not hold off the winner. SEDUCTIVE U S A unhurried early to be well back at the tail of the field, closed ground to the far turn to commence his rally in earnest while circling five wide and closed ground down the lane to be best of the rest. PARROT HEAD prompted the pace while racing three wide throughout, loomed up midway on the final bend and failed to sustain his bid down he stretch. FRED'STWIRLINCANDY sped to the lead the first time by the stand, dueled on the pace from the rail to the top of the lane and weakened late in the drive. WHISKEY NOT WINE broke tardy from the gate giving a length or so at the start and raced near the rear never posing a threat. COLOSI went evenly never menacing at any point.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 84. Claiming Purse 19000. (PLUS UP TO $3,800 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AUTOSTRADA broke alertly to be on the pace away from the gate, settled two wide to press the pace, took control midway on the turn, repelled the challengers in upper stretch and dug-in gamely down the lane in a determined victory. TRUE BLUE SKY unhurried early, rallied down the backside into contention, made a strong sweeping move from five wide in the turn to collar the frontrunners and battled down to the wire in a game effort to be second best in the end. HOURGLASS FIGURE tracked the leaders from the second flight in between rivals, rallied well down the lane but could not gain ground on the top pair. KEEP THE BLING rated in mid-pack most of the way and showed late interest in the stretch with a mild bid. AUSTIN CITY GIRL stalked the lead from three wide most of the way, loomed up boldly at the quarter pole and flattened out in the lane. GREY HALO chased the leaders in the second flight from the rail to be well placed in the far turn but failed to respond when called upon for the drive. TEXAS TIDELANDS sped up to take the lead into the first turn from the rail, dueled on the pace to the far turn and weakened turning for home. GRASS QUEEN trailed most of the way and passed tired rivals in the stretch. HONOR GIVEN went evenly never posing a threat. CHEROKEE SUMMER was never a factor.
